ximately  corporate and franchisee locations in north america europe latin america africa asia australia the caribbean the middle east and new zealand contents  history  early years  the hertz corporation  key executives  hertz global holdings inc  headquarters relocation  locations  fleet  specialty cars  green collection and electric cars  hertz  car sharing  simply wheelz and advantage  advertising  let hertz put you in the driver’s seat  john f kennedy assassination  oj simpson  lowfloor passenger bus  heavy equipment rental  references historyedit early yearsedit the company was founded by walter l jacobs in  who started a car rental operation in chicago with a dozen model t ford cars in  jacobs sold it to john d hertz who made it a subsidiary of his yellow truck and coach manufacturing company and renamed it hertz driveurself system he sold a controlling interest in the yellow truck and coach manufacturing company and hence also hertz driveurself to general motors in  who then purchased the remaining shares in  hertz arranged for the omnibus corporation which he also owned to purchase the car rental business back from gm in  he sold all the omnibus corporations public transport interests the same year changed its name to the hertz corporation and floated it on the new york stock exchange the following year the hertz corporationedit in  the new corporation bought new york truck leasing company metropolitan distributors in  the hertz corporation became a wholly owned subsidiary of rca but was operated as a separate entity in  hertz joined and was acquired by ual corporation on december   hertz was sold to park ridge corporation which was then owned by ford motor company and members of hertz senior management in  volvo north america corporation invested in park ridge corporation on june   ford issued a notice that hertz would be let loose in an initial public offering on september   it was announced it was to be sold to private equity companies clayton dubilier  rice the carlyle group and merrill lynch global private equity for  billion in cash and debt acquisition the sale was completed on december   this private equity group took hertz public on november   on january   hertz announced the acquisition of used cars dealer british car auctions bca for an undisclosed sum in november  hertz introduced expressrent kiosks at a number of locations this was the first large scale car rental kiosk deployment in the us using a live agent assistant via video chat on january   it was reported that hertz shares had jumped in value by  after the reported purchase of  million shares by billionaire carl icahn in what was believed to be a hostile takeover attempt in response to icahn’s reported share purchase the hertz board reportedly stated that it would issue one preferred share for each current share in what is referred to as a “poison pill” response key executivesedit michel taride in  kathryn v marinello was named president and chief executive officer and a member of the board of directors of the hertz corporation in december  tom kennedy has served as senior executive vice president and chief financial officer since december  he is responsible for all aspects of financial management encompassing treasury tax risk management accounting financial reporting business planning corporate development and corporate policies and procedures tyler best is the executive vice president and chief information officer since january  he oversees the company’s global information technology it functions alexandria marren is the executive vice president north american rental car operations since august  michel taride was appointed executive vice president and president of hertz international ltd in january  taride has managed fleet planning and remarketing functions of hertz international since december  hertz global holdings incedit in april  hertz and dollarthrifty automotive group announced an agreement under which hertz was to acquire dollarthrifty 