ollar and thrifty brands from approximately  corporate and franchisee locations in north america europe latin america africa asia australia the caribbean the middle east and new zealand contents  history  early years  the hertz corporation  key executives  hertz global holdings inc  headquarters relocation  locations  fleet  specialty cars  green collection and electric cars  hertz  car sharing  simply wheelz and advantage  advertising  let hertz put you in the driver’s seat  john f kennedy assassination  oj simpson  lowfloor passenger bus  heavy equipment rental  references historyedit early yearsedit the company was founded by walter l jacobs in  who started a car rental operation in chicago with a dozen model t ford cars in  jacobs sold it to john d hertz who made it a subsidiary of his yellow truck and coach manufacturing company and renamed it hertz driveurself system he sold a controlling interest in the yellow truck and coach manufacturing company and hence also hertz driveurself to general motors in  who then purchased the remaining shares in  hertz arranged for the omnibus corporation which he also owned to purchase the car rental business back from gm in  he sold all the omnibus corporations public transport interests the same year changed its name to the hertz corporation and floated it on the new york stock exchange the following year the hertz corporationedit in  the new corporation bought new york truck leasing company metropolitan distributors in  the hertz corporation became a wholly owned subsidiary of rca but was operated as a separate entity in  hertz joined and was acquired by ual corporation on december   hertz was sold to park ridge corporation which was then owned by ford motor company and members of hertz senior management in  volvo north america corporation invested in park ridge corporation on june   ford issued a notice that hertz would be let loose in an initial public offering on september   it was announced it was to be sold to private equity companies clayton dubilier  rice the carlyle group and merrill lynch global private equity for  billion in cash and debt acquisition the sale was completed on december   this private equity group took hertz public on november   on january   hertz announced the acquisition of used cars dealer british car auctions bca for an undisclosed sum in november  hertz introduced expressrent kiosks at a number of locations this was the first large scale car rental kiosk deployment in the us using a live agent assistant via video chat on january   it was reported that hertz shares had jumped in value by  after the reported purchase of  million shares by billionaire carl icahn in what was believed to be a hostile takeover attempt in response to icahn’s reported share purchase the hertz board reportedly stated that it would issue one preferred share for each current share in what is referred to as a “poison pill” response key executivesedit michel taride in  kathryn v marinello was named president and chief executive officer and a member of the board of directors of the hertz corporation in december  tom kennedy has served as senior executive vice president and chief financial officer since december  he is responsible for all aspects of financial management encompassing treasury tax risk management accounting financial reporting business planning corporate development and corporate policies and procedures tyler best is the executive vice president and chief information officer since january  he oversees the company’s global information technology it functions alexandria marren is the executive vice president north american rental car operations since august  michel taride was appointed executive vice president and president of hertz international ltd in january  taride has managed fleet planning and remarketing functions of hertz international since december  hertz global holdings incedit in april  hertz and dollarthrifty automotive group announced an agreement under which hertz was to acquire dollarthrifty for a purchase price of us per share subject to shareholder approval in a mix of cash and hertz common stock dollarthrifty investors in tulsa oklahoma rejected this us bid from hertz on september   dollarthrifty subsequently announced on october   that it had taken itself off the market because it did not receive any proposals that would pass antitrust review on august   hertz announced for the second time its intention to acquire dollarthrifty subject to ftc approval in this case for us this merger would yield combined annual sales of us the deal was concluded in november  and resulted in a combined  locations in approximately  countries headquarters relocationedit on may   hertz executives alongside florida governor rick scott announced the company would be relocating its worldwide headquarters from park ridge new jersey to estero florida it will be located on the southeast corner of the intersection of williams road and us highway  south tamiami trail though some operations will still occur in its old headquarters in park ridge locationsedit hertz office on the island of marthas vineyard hertz operates in  countries outside the us hertz has companyoperated locations in  countries the rest being franchises as of december update the company had approximately  staffed rental locations in the united states and around  staffed rental locations internationally overland west is the largest hertz licensee in north america operating  car rental and  car sales locations in  states wilford gwilliam purchased the hertz franchise in  he later sold it to devere j sparrow who led the organization until  when he sold it to his soninlaw jerry h petersen jerry grew the business from just a few rental locations and one sales location to what it is today and still serves as the owner president and ceo fleetedit the hertz fleet consists of a wide majority of vehicle manufacturers with the majority being gm products luxury cars are provided by mercedes infiniti and cadillac previously due to hertzs affiliation with ford the rental fleet of most locations consisted of ford and its brands such as mazda volvo mercury and lincoln along with various others mostly korean and japanese as of december update the company has over  cars in the us and a rental fleet in its international operations of over  cars exclusive of its licensees fleet specialty carsedit in  hertz engaged racing and automotive designer carroll shelby to develop an exclusive version of his modified ford mustang one thousand gth mustangs were built and ultimately sold once their rental use had ended however many of them were missing the matching engine some customers would rent the car for a weekend and swap out the highperformance engine with a base version  cu in  l v engine inspections upon return of the rental unit were not common place so nobody found out until the car was due for service by that time there was no way to track down the engine thief the socalled rentaracer program in the lates was available in selected locations and the fleet also included corvettes jaguar xkes and amc amxs in  the th anniversary of the original gth hertz introduced the shelby mustang gth as part of the fun collection at select locations this was followed in  with a convertible version of the gth  saw  chevrolet corvettes badged as zhz available from selected us airports the following year  convertible zhzs joined the fleet both were finished in hertz corporate yellow with a central black stripe in  hertz paired with penske and ford to manufacture speciallymodified blackandyellow  ford mustang gt premium coupes that were individually numbered for their fleets at select us airports all of hertzs us specialty cars featured sirius satellite radio hertzs neverlost navigation system and other features that may not be equipped or at least may cost extra on their standardclass vehicles green collection and electric carsedit hertz launched its green collection in september  with environmentally friendly vehicles including the toyota prius ford fusion buick lacrosse toyota camry and hyundai sonata all feature environmental protection agency epa highway fuel efficiency ratings of  mpg‑us  l km  mpg‑imp or better on the highway in early  hertz launched its global hybrid rental program in conjunction with a  million donation to the national park foundation hertz has an agreement with nissan to bring the nissan leaf electric car to certain us and european locations hertz said it also will supply electrics and plugin hybrids from other manufacturers including general motors toyota and mitsubishi hertz  car sharingedit hertz  formerly hertz on demand and earlier connect by hertz is the hertz corporation’s global car sharing service launched in december  and currently operates in outside of the united states in select cities in europe and in sydney australia hertz  shut down its united states operations including university campuses in  and had previously shut operations in select cities in years prior to the full shutdown on university campuses hertz  offered vehicles in the personal social and jet set collections following the restructuring the hertz  service now mainly focuses on hourly van hire at retail outlets in the remaining countries such as ikea homebase bq and costco wholesale after a recent fleet replacement scheme the majority of the vehicles are vw transporter vans in mainland europe and renault master lwb vans in the united kingdom hertz  remains available as a fleet management service for the likes of local government offices where a fleet of company cars is necessary and the hertz car sharing service makes for easier booking support and management for these large fleets after the united states closure of the hertz  service a similar offering remains available within the united kingdom located at universities and colleges around the country a typical example of the university fleet is at imperial college london where a nissan leaf kwh ford fiesta  auto and ford focus  manual are available for use by students staff and the general public at both hourly and daily rates customers book online at the hertz  website or using the hertz  android and ios app where they can locate available vehicles and reserve them subject to a  preauthorization on the users credit or debit card  minute prior to the booking start time the customer is allowed access to the vehicle the access code will be sent by both email and sms which they can input on a pin entry panel located on the drivers side of the vehicle windshield alternatively if the user has been issued with one they can gain access using their rfid entry pass the keys to the vehicle are located on a tether beside the steering wheel and are only used to operate the engine ignition locking the vehicle during a booking session continues to be done via the pin entry pad leaving the keys attached to the tether at all times a fuel card or electric vehicle charging card is located in the sun visor and the cost of gasoline electricity or diesel is covered by hertz the user simply pays the permile charge regardless of how much fuel was purchased for example in the united kingdom there is no electric vehicle mileage charge a pmile charge in cars and pmile charge in vans all users are required to return the vehicle at the end of the booking on time clean inside and out empty and with at least a quarter tank of fuel failure to do so will result in penalties for the inconvenience to the next user simply wheelz and advantageedit for premerger history see advantage rent a car in  hertz launched subbrand simply wheelz to address economyminded and leisuremarket customers in orlando florida the subbrand was colocated within and utilized the fleet and other assets of the parent brand and channeled reservations and customerservice through a streamlined web frontend resembling those of lowcostcarrier airlines to its existing systems hertz outbid enterprise rentacar acquiring the assets of bankrupt advantage rent a car system in early  the simply wheelz subbrand and website were then rebranded as advantage rentacar on august   hertz announced that it agreed to sell the us advantage business to franchise services of north america and macquarie capital as a divestiture to receive regulatory approval of hertzs acquisition of dollar thrifty automotive group announced at the same time and to convert foreign advantage locations to the thrifty brand on december   advantage rent a car was acquired by macquarie capital advertisingedit let hertz put you in the driver’s seatedit in  the advertising firm of norman craig  kummel nck was selected as the new advertising agency for hertz nck developed the slogan “hertz puts you in the driver’s seat” which was first used commercially in september  nck quickly changed the wording to “let hertz put you in the driver’s seat” by october  popular a cappella quartet the hilos sang the hertz song for the commercials hertz used the line in the early s in print signs and television the series is listed as number  in the top  advertising campaigns of the th century by advertising age magazine john f kennedy assassinationedit hertz billboard on the texas school book depository roof in  a large billboard advertising hertz was on the roof of the texas school book depository in dealey plaza during the assassination of president john f kennedy on november   the billboard was removed in  oj simpsonedit oj simpson appeared prominently in ads for the company the company set the trend of hiring black athletes as sponsors of various brands in  oj simpson became a staple in american households with his hertz commercials one spot from the mids showed simpson former football star as he was running through an airport terminal wearing a threepiece business suit and carrying a briefcase and leaping over rows of departure lounge seats trying to get to his hertz rental car a woman yelled go oj go the tagline of the ad as spoken by oj was hertz the superstar in rentacar in later years and through the s he appeared with golf legend arnold palmer the pair was joined by the early s by actress jamie lee curtis the relationship between hertz and simpson ended in  following simpsons arrest for the murder of nicole brown simpson and ron goldman lowfloor passenger busedit a low floor hertz bus at ohare international airport in chicago a significant hertzled technology was the development in north america of the lowfloor passenger coach until the early st century most large hertz lots were linked to airports they served by small fleets of firmoperated transit buses many hertz locations used the rapid transit series whose high floor and stairs made loading of baggage difficult and rendered access to wheelchair and ecvusing customers difficult or impossible a large potential contract from hertz led gillig brothers of hayward california to invest in a radical redesign of the city bus that offered a floor only a foot off of the ground lower when pneumatically kneeled from the front of the bus between the front wheels up to the rear axle the low floor and additional space freed by the redesign initially titled the hlf by hertz greatly reduced loading and unloading time increased convenience and were for a time exclusive to hertz the bus was subsequently marketed as the gillig low floor and is widely deployed by us public transportation agencies heavy equipment rentaledit hertz also maintained a heavy equipment rental division known as the hertz equipment rental corporation aka herc until july   herc started operating in  with its first location in houston tx it was headquartered in park ridge new jersey united states in  hertz announced that they would separate their equipment rental division through a tax free spin off the split was completed on june   and on july   hertz equipment rental corporation became an independently publicly traded company called herc rentals inc herc has more than  branches throughout the united states canada the european union and china referencesedit  hertz global announces kathryn v marinello to become president and chief executive officer irhertzcom retrieved may     hertz says over  jobs to go bbc news january   retrieved december     a b hertz global holdings inc company profile yahoo finance retrieved january      us car rental market auto rental news retrieved may     the hertz corporation history funding universe retrieved may     about hertz company overview irhertzcom retrieved may     a b hertz history hertz corporation retrieved january     andrew ross sorkin september   private investors to buy hertz for  billion new york times retrieved december     hertz acquires used car dealer bca january   retrieved february     stacy collett hertz improves customer experience with friendlier kiosks cio retrieved march     carl icahn is loading up on hertz and shares are popping business insider january      auto rental news december     auto rental news january    hertz names evp of north american rental operations auto rental news august    michael taride forbes april    hertz signs definitive agreement to acquire dollar thrifty press release dollar thrifty automotive group april   archived from the original on january   retrieved august     bliss jeff clothier mark november   avis may have to sell assets to get thrifty proposal bloomberg retrieved november     dollar thrifty takes itself off the market bloomberg businessweek associated press october     moss linda hertz buys dollar thrifty northjerseycom   terlep sharon kendall brent november   hertz to get approval of dollarthrifty deal the wall street journal p b   hertz global holdings inc htz reuters retrieved august     httpwwwoverlandwestcomaboutushtml  nolan bruce  amc amx  hertz rent a racer retrieved december     rentaracer hertz and the muscle car era fossilcars march   retrieved december     grant john  the green marketing manifesto wiley isbn  retrieved january     h